Sunny- lake choppy- wind W 12 mph
Sunny- choppy- 7" rain in last 3 days making the water level high.
Cloudy- lake choppy- still rain off and on almost every day- and wind is southwest at 7mph.
Sunny- lake rough- wind S 15 mph.
Cloudy- wind south at 4 to 6 mph- and the water is calm.
Sunny- wind southwest at 4-6 mph- and water very calm but looked dirty with a lot of scum and cut up weeds floating.
Cloudy- wind northeast at 6-8 mph- and the water is rippling and cleaner.
Sunny- wind northwest at 10-15- water rough- and the temperature is 65 degrees F.
Mostly sunny- northwest wind at 6 mph- and the water is calm.
Mostly cloudy- south wind at 6-12 mph- water choppy and very green.
Sunny- south wind at 8-15- and the water is rough.
Cloudy- southwest wind at 10-15- and the water is choppy.
Cloudy and foggy- wind SE 4- water calm.
Sunny- S wind- scum on top of water- bad thunderstorm on 8/13/87.
Mostly sunny- winds S 15-25 mph- water very rough.
Sunny- wind SW at 8 mph- some water-skiers today.
Mostly cloudy- wind SW at 10 mph- water rough- rained off and on for the past few days.
Mostly sunny- wind SE @ 8 mph- water choppy- last report for the season.
Wind SE @ 2-4- sunny- lake calm- water looks scummy.
Wind W-6 mph- lake calm- temp. 65 F- sunny
Wind S 10-15 mph- lake choppy- partly cloudy.
Wind NE 8-10- lake choppy- temp 55 F- sunny.  Water level: very low.

Foggy- calm- 50 F- lt. green algae in water
Wind SW 12 mph- sunny- ripples- level ft.+ high from severe storms
Sunny- NW wind 15 mph- was rough- getting back to normal
Sunny- wind W 6 mph- lake calm
Sunny- S wind 10-12 mph- lake has lots of ripples.
Sunny- NE wind 8-10 mph- lake has ripples
Sunny- NW wind 6-8 mph- getting green from algae

Cloudy- NE wind 6-10 mph- lake choppy
Sunny- SW wind 6-8 mph- lake calm- rain on + off last 2 days

Sunny- NE wind 4 mph- water has ripples- last reading

Sunny- lake rough- W wind 15 gusting to 25 mph
Sunny- calm- S wind 3 mph- 60 F

Cloudy- windy- and the temperature is 55 degrees.  8.1" of rain from 8/13-9/18.
Cloudy- windy- and the temperature is 48 degrees.  4.2" of rain from 9/13-10/19.  Lake level being lowered for dam repairs
Cloudy- temperature is 65 degrees- and the rain gauge readings from 8/15-8/22 is 0.5 inches.
Air temp 71 F.  Rain gauge reading from 7/10-8/6 is 2.05 inches.
Rain gauge reading from 8/6-9/24 is 3.7 inches.
Beautiful day- air temp 75 F.  Rain gauge reading from 9/24-10/2 is 3 inches.
Weather is in 80's with no wind.
Sunny and windy- temperature is 62 degrees
Rain gauge reading from 6/1/97 to 6/30/97 =8.5 inches
Rain gauge reading from 7/1 to 7/31=5.5 inches
Rain gauge reading from 8/1 to 8/26=7.5 inches
Rain gauge reading from 8/3 to 9/30=4.5 inches.
Little windy. Rain gauge reading from 9/2/2000 to 10/2/2000 = 5.25".
Too many high powered speed boats and jet skis on weekends that disturb the water quality- clarity and tons of chopped off weeds!  Noise from certain speed boats a problem also.

Rain gauge reading 3.25 inches from 6/1-6/25.  A lot of algae bloom in the beginning of the summer.  Also- more and different weeds are growing in our lake.  Geese are still a problem as are high powered boats for shore erosion. // Couldn't complete the DO test because a lot of particles.  Seemed to have a lot of trouble with oxygen testing.  It was so very different from other years.  We weren't aware the sodium thiosulfate was to be refrigerated.  Could this be the problem.  It has small black particles in it.

We have a problem with over-abundant weeds and foreign weeds.  Still a problem with geese.  Rain gauge 4.6 inches from 6/26/02 to 7/30/02.  // With our last 30 + 35 foot depths- the wind picked up and with boat traffic- our DO testing couldn't be completed.

Found  a lot of tiny zebra mussels on weeds when lifting up anchor.  Rain gauge from 8/4-8/28 is 5 inches.  // We had trouble with the syringe and for taking the last oxygen sample the rubber got stuck.  Need a new one for next month.  Temp at lab - iced.
DEEP HOLE - BASELINE LAKES SPRING PROTOCOL
DEEP HOLE     100% cloud cover with winds out of SE at 15mph and no prior rain.  Total phos sampled at .5 meter.  Water color clear with no algal bloom obvious.  Bottom at 14 meters.
Very warm and dry spring thus far.  Plants are well ahead.

DEEP HOLE     Wind out of N at 10 mph with 30% cloud cover and no prior rain.  Chla- TP- Temp- and DO sampled at .5 m with integrated sampler.  Water color dark green with no algal bloom obvious.  Bottom at 14.5 meters.
water quality samples taken today and sent monday.  Lots of Sunday afternoon boat traffic.
DEEP HOLE     Wind out of NE at 5 mph with 40% cloud cover.  No algal development apparent.  Site depth 14.5 meters.  Integrated sampler at 2m.
Nights have been cooler and reduced boat traffic.  The lake has really cleared up.  Nice sunny day in the low 70s.

DEEP HOLE     Wind out of NE at 5 mph with 0% cloud cover and prior rain.  Full LTTM suite sampled with integrated sampler.  Water color light brown with no algal bloom evident.  Bottom at 14.5 meters.
Christina Hodge participated in monitoring.  30% cloud cover with wind out of NE at 5-10 mph.  Algal bloom not obvious.  Total phos. and chla sampled @ 1meter.  Bottom at 13 meters.
Winds strong out of the south.  Warm Sunday morning.  Karen and I rowed out to get sample and Secchi.

No cloud cover winds out of N at 10 mph with  greater than 2"  rain 3 days earlier.  Water color clear and dark green with no algal bloom obvious.  Total phos and chla sampled at .5 meters.  Plenty of boating- good clarity 21' secchi.  Bottom at 14 meters.
TOM FLASH AND WALLY PAGE TOOK READING WITH ME JUST BEFORE OUR SUNDAY MORNING WATER SKI.

column1: DAY WAS PARTLY CLOUDY AND IN 70S.

column2: nice day good for data collection.  Eric grabbed sample and took Secchi for me.
Dave- Wally Page and Tom Flash took reading just before our Sunday AM water ski.  Nice calm day.  Good for both.

30% cloud cover with wind out of S. at 10-15 mph with 4-5" rain in the preceding 5 days.  Total phos and chla samples at 0.5 meters.  Water color deep green and clear with a slight algal bloom obvious.  Bottom at 14 meters.

Wind out of SW at 15 mph with prior rain and 100% cloud cover.  TP sampled with integrated sampler.  Water color brown with no algal bloom obvious.  Windy- thunder- no time for complete profile- rain.

Wind out of NW at 15-20 mph with no prior rain and 5% cloud cover.  TP- Chla sampled with integrated sampler (0.5m).  Water color clear brown wth no algal bloom obvious.  Zooplankton abundant.  Bottom at 14.5 meters.
Boat fixed and able to go out now.
Wally and Tom along.  Nice day

Winds out of NW at 15-20 mph- no prior rain with 50% cloud cover.  TP- Chla- and LLTM suite sampled with integrated sampler.  Water color brown/green with a slight algal bloom present.  Bottom at 14.5 meters.
Nice day.  Wally's boat taken out today.
Wind out of SE at 20 mph 0% cloud cover and no prior rain.  Water color clear/brown with no algal bloom obvious.  TP- Chla- DO/Temp- Secchi sampled.  Integrated sampler used.  Bottom at 14.5 meters.
lots of rain this summer and very warm
nice day for sample.  Last rain was heavy about 1.25" on Friday afternoon.
A windy day and part overcast.  Impressed with the lake and how clear the water looked.  Memorial day Monday.
Warm sunny day- Labor Day Monday
